reviewText:
Stylish, inspired and solid, nicely challenging and thoroughly sudaesque. It was panned by critics, but I found it a very enjoyable action game. I liked it more than, say, Metal Gear Rising, which, despite also having had a lot of fun with, I was too bored to beat.

Liked about it:
- Suda51 antics first and foremost, no need to mince words here, I guess;
- quality (if generic) battle system‚Äîlast second dodge, some minor shooting mechanics, a generic but entertaining upgrade mechanic;
- challenge;
- visuals‚Äîboth aesthetically and, in fact, technically;
- most of the characters;
- I even managed to have fun with the silly Mondo Girls minigame.

I love Suda Goichi's style, but I don't like his game design. No More Heroes was strange and limited, even Killer7 shined despite its somewhat tedious gameplay and not due to it. Here, though, I loved both; I really do feel that KiD is style and substance both.
